        <div class="gs-intro">
          <h2>Get Started</h2>
          <p>Participating in the Living Atlas is accomplished in two ways- using content and contributing content. The well-ordered, thematic gallery is makes it easy to discover items of interest and on-demand accessibility, from a variety of devices, enables use where and when you need it.  Two contribution applications make contributing a straight-forward process.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="gs-item" style="padding-bottom: 30px;">
          <img src="/en/living-atlas/img/get-started-use.png" alt="" align="left" style="padding-right: 15px;"/>
          <div class="item-content">
            <h4>Use</h4>
            <p style="width:80%;">Collections, organized by theme, make exploring and discovering ready to use maps and layers efficient and straightforward. Use these maps, data layers, tools, services, and apps to enhance your everyday work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="gs-item" style="padding-bottom: 60px;">
          <img src="/en/living-atlas/img/get-started-contribute.png" alt="" align="left" style="padding-right: 15px;" />
          <div class="item-content">
            <h4>Contribute</h4>
            <p style="width:80%;">The Living Atlas is a collaborative effort between GIS users, Esri, and its partners around the world. Whether it’s contributing authoritative data or nominating your maps and apps, there is a way for you to get involved.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
